x4freetext: A self-supporting natural silicon targets with
thicknesses from 50 to 100 mug/cm**2. The targets
showed a slight contamination of oxygen and a
considerable build-up of the carbon content during the
alpha-particles were identified with delta-E-E counter
telescopes, which consisted of a thin surface barrier
silicon detector and a thick Li-drifted silicon
detector for most of the measurements.
The corrections for the target contaminations were
determined from separate measurements using Si, SiO(2)
*By authors*.The cross sections were normalised to the
elastic scattering yields monitored at a fixed angle.
The relative errors of the double differential cross
sections are estimated to be 6% at higher and up to 15%
at lower beam energies. The error of the absolute
normalisation is of the order of 8%.
